    "body": "Problem:  Marks are not adjusted unloading a buffer that doesn't exist\r\n          on disk. E.g. extmarks are still valid (and will be beyond the\r\n          end of the buffer if the buffer is reloaded), even though the\r\n          text is lost.\r\nSolution: Adjust marks for a cleared buffer when unloading a buffer that\r\n          doesn't exist on disk.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-18T10:53:01Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Looks like this also clears `b:` vars, buffer-local mappings and user commands.\r\n\r\nDunno if it'll be a problem, but maybe worth updating `:h :map-local`, `:h b:`?",
