        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Looks like this also clears b: vars, buffer-local mappings and user commands.\r\n\r\nYes, is there any reason to keep these around? Even if it is re-used internally, isn't it a new buffer for all intents and purposes after a non-file buffer is unloaded?",
