        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Largely depends on how plugins are using it, I suppose.\r\n\r\nE.g: a plugin maps a `nofile`/`acwrite` buffer to some (non-file) resource; reloading it has the plugin repopulate the content from that resource. If `acwrite`, it may even be that `:write` is specially handled (e.g: updates a network file).\r\n\r\nIn that case it may make sense to keep the vars and such, like file buffers do; only difference is that the underlying resource is something else, and a plugin is managing the content.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-16T16:57:13Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39118#issuecomment-4261912551",
