        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> > Looks like this also clears b: vars, buffer-local mappings and user commands.\r\n> \r\n> Yes, is there any reason to keep these around? Even if it is re-used internally, isn't it a new buffer for all intents and purposes after a non-file buffer is unloaded?\r\n\r\nIn the case this is meant to address, can the buffer be re-loaded under the same buffer number?\r\n\r\n> I'm not totally against the idea of clearing the extmarks tbh (though I'm also not sure what the impact will be); most of my concern was for the mappings and other stuff.\r\n\r\nClearing the extmarks should make sense.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-16T22:29:25Z",
